1
00:00:22,464 --> 00:00:26,432
♪Should we forget yesterday's sorrows♪

2
00:00:26,432 --> 00:00:29,728
♪And the dazed confusion♪

3
00:00:30,976 --> 00:00:33,681
♪Should we let go of♪

4
00:00:33,681 --> 00:00:35,904
♪The stubborn madness♪

5
00:00:35,904 --> 00:00:39,072
♪And naive recklessness now♪

6
00:00:40,192 --> 00:00:43,840
♪Those years, those faces♪

7
00:00:44,992 --> 00:00:48,763
♪Those old scars we can't erase♪

8
00:00:49,824 --> 00:00:52,460
♪Tears streaming, facing the light♪

9
00:00:53,152 --> 00:00:57,594
♪Piercing the sorrow within♪

10
00:01:08,716 --> 00:01:12,736
♪The road ahead's long,
stumbling all the way♪

11
00:01:13,536 --> 00:01:18,076
♪The wounds we've borne
are medals hidden within♪

12
00:01:18,336 --> 00:01:22,391
♪Standing alone on an open plain♪

13
00:01:23,168 --> 00:01:26,851
♪We gaze at the stars♪

14
00:01:31,228 --> 00:01:34,816
=The Dream Maker=

15
00:01:35,032 --> 00:01:37,880
=Episode 22=

16
00:01:38,776 --> 00:01:41,856
Desheng, lying for him

17
00:01:42,696 --> 00:01:43,735
is not good for him.

18
00:01:53,095 --> 00:01:56,455
Decheng, I've never lied to you.

19
00:02:05,255 --> 00:02:05,975
Okay.

20
00:02:08,096 --> 00:02:08,655
I believe you.

21
00:02:15,055 --> 00:02:15,816
I'm telling you.

22
00:02:16,256 --> 00:02:18,495
Don't mess around outside anymore.

23
00:02:19,175 --> 00:02:20,136
Find yourself a job.

24
00:02:20,440 --> 00:02:21,080
Do you hear me?

25
00:02:22,816 --> 00:02:24,175
I've told you many times.

26
00:02:31,224 --> 00:02:31,832
Sister-in-law.

27
00:02:32,256 --> 00:02:33,016
Misunderstanding.

28
00:02:33,256 --> 00:02:33,775
It's alright.

29
00:02:34,215 --> 00:02:34,895
That's good.

30
00:02:35,136 --> 00:02:36,175
Stay for dinner.

31
00:02:36,215 --> 00:02:36,976
No, thanks.

32
00:02:37,136 --> 00:02:38,335
I've got some work to handle.

33
00:02:38,576 --> 00:02:39,096
I have to go.

34
00:02:39,215 --> 00:02:39,935
Desheng, I'm off.

35
00:02:39,935 --> 00:02:40,735
- Leaving now?
- Yes.

36
00:02:40,735 --> 00:02:41,576
- Take care.
- Bye.

37
00:02:41,735 --> 00:02:43,696
However busy you are, remember to eat.

38
00:02:48,376 --> 00:02:49,455
You brat!

39
00:02:49,816 --> 00:02:50,895
Got some nerve now, huh?

40
00:02:51,576 --> 00:02:52,816
Tell the truth or not?

41
00:02:52,895 --> 00:02:54,696
Say it!

42
00:02:54,856 --> 00:02:56,096
Tell me the truth!

43
00:02:56,576 --> 00:02:57,136
Tell me.

44
00:02:57,215 --> 00:02:58,935
You came back so late last night.

45
00:02:58,976 --> 00:03:00,055
Was it you?

46
00:03:01,016 --> 00:03:02,136
I've told you.

47
00:03:02,775 --> 00:03:03,816
It wasn't me.

48
00:03:03,976 --> 00:03:05,935
I didn't do any one
of those he mentioned!

49
00:03:06,016 --> 00:03:07,495
Then why did he say it was you?

50
00:03:07,536 --> 00:03:08,775
How would I know? Go ask him!

51
00:03:08,816 --> 00:03:10,016
I'm asking you right now!

52
00:03:10,455 --> 00:03:11,215
You won't say it?

53
00:03:11,296 --> 00:03:12,416
You brat!

54
00:03:12,495 --> 00:03:13,495
Dad, stop hitting him.

55
00:03:13,536 --> 00:03:14,775
Zhiqiang says it wasn't him!

56
00:03:14,856 --> 00:03:15,696
- Dad!
- Dad!

57
00:03:15,735 --> 00:03:16,895
You'll hurt him!

58
00:03:16,935 --> 00:03:17,775
You, kneel down!

59
00:03:18,096 --> 00:03:19,696
All of you, kneel down!

60
00:03:21,455 --> 00:03:23,905
Anything happens to him,
none of you will get away with it.

61
00:03:24,536 --> 00:03:25,048
Got it?

62
00:03:25,368 --> 00:03:25,895
Say it!

63
00:03:30,968 --> 00:03:31,495
Right.

64
00:03:32,696 --> 00:03:34,816
In his eyes,
every bad thing is my fault.

65
00:03:35,576 --> 00:03:37,215
Just because I beat up 'monkeys' before.

66
00:03:37,816 --> 00:03:39,136
He is just a 'monkey' secretary!

67
00:03:39,136 --> 00:03:40,016
Zhiqiang!

68
00:03:40,296 --> 00:03:41,576
Dad!

69
00:03:41,816 --> 00:03:42,376
Stop hitting!

70
00:03:42,576 --> 00:03:43,775
Stop hitting! Stop!

71
00:03:43,816 --> 00:03:44,696
Didn't I warn you?

72
00:03:44,775 --> 00:03:45,735
Didn't I tell you?

73
00:03:45,935 --> 00:03:47,096
Never talk like that!

74
00:03:47,136 --> 00:03:47,735
Zhiqiang!

75
00:03:47,976 --> 00:03:48,416
Zhiqiang!

76
00:03:48,416 --> 00:03:49,136
You, kneel down.

77
00:03:49,256 --> 00:03:50,296
He thinks he's tough now?

78
00:03:50,296 --> 00:03:51,064
What does he want?

79
00:03:51,672 --> 00:03:52,696
Zhiqiang, put it down.

80
00:03:52,935 --> 00:03:53,495
Please, stop.

81
00:03:53,536 --> 00:03:54,495
Mom, stay out of this.

82
00:03:57,464 --> 00:03:58,392
Where are you going?

83
00:03:58,655 --> 00:03:59,215
Zhiqiang!

84
00:03:59,696 --> 00:04:00,615
Are you crazy?

85
00:04:01,816 --> 00:04:03,136
What are you trying to do?

86
00:04:03,175 --> 00:04:03,935
Zhiqiang!

87
00:04:06,655 --> 00:04:07,976
Nothing I say matters anyway.

88
00:04:09,455 --> 00:04:10,335
If you don't trust me,

89
00:04:10,895 --> 00:04:12,016
just kill me!

90
00:04:25,816 --> 00:04:27,095
I'm asking you one last time.

91
00:04:27,215 --> 00:04:28,295
Tell me the truth.

92
00:04:29,415 --> 00:04:31,295
Why did you come back

93
00:04:32,136 --> 00:04:33,295
so late last night?

94
00:04:34,200 --> 00:04:34,715
I...

95
00:04:35,640 --> 00:04:39,136
I was drinking
and playing cards with Xiaohai.

96
00:04:40,936 --> 00:04:41,895
I fell asleep.

97
00:04:44,775 --> 00:04:45,655
When I woke up,

98
00:04:45,696 --> 00:04:46,535
I came back.

99
00:04:51,936 --> 00:04:53,855
You brat!

100
00:04:54,496 --> 00:04:55,616
Got some nerve now, huh?

101
00:04:56,335 --> 00:04:57,496
Dare wave a knife around!

102
00:05:02,855 --> 00:05:03,448
Darling.

103
00:05:04,280 --> 00:05:05,295
Go get some bruise oil.

104
00:05:06,816 --> 00:05:07,295
Okay.

105
00:05:07,655 --> 00:05:08,095
Get up.

106
00:05:30,616 --> 00:05:32,056
I've told you already.

107
00:05:33,535 --> 00:05:35,376
You can't talk about Decheng like that.

108
00:05:35,775 --> 00:05:36,936
He's the Secretary.

109
00:05:38,295 --> 00:05:40,056
He's the secretary for all of us.

110
00:05:40,655 --> 00:05:42,215
What Secretary?

111
00:05:43,975 --> 00:05:44,696
Dad, just think...

112
00:05:47,775 --> 00:05:48,816
Think about it.

113
00:05:50,415 --> 00:05:51,936
All these years in Yuehai,

114
00:05:52,256 --> 00:05:53,415
have we got any benefit?

115
00:05:53,775 --> 00:05:55,455
Aren't we still struggling?

116
00:06:01,775 --> 00:06:04,895
Dad, I'm your own son.

117
00:06:05,855 --> 00:06:07,016
Don't you know?

118
00:06:07,895 --> 00:06:09,736
I wouldn't dare hurt anyone.

119
00:06:09,775 --> 00:06:11,095
How could you suspect me?

120
00:06:12,816 --> 00:06:13,335
Zhiqiang.

121
00:06:16,215 --> 00:06:17,176
You two, get back!

122
00:06:18,056 --> 00:06:19,736
Never say a word about tonight, got it?

123
00:06:19,895 --> 00:06:20,616
Go back!

124
00:06:20,736 --> 00:06:21,256
Get up.

125
00:06:21,295 --> 00:06:21,775
Go back.

126
00:06:21,855 --> 00:06:23,376
Get up.

127
00:06:24,655 --> 00:06:25,136
Let's go.

128
00:07:06,040 --> 00:07:09,048
(Cinema)

129
00:07:09,048 --> 00:07:10,415
(No Credit)

130
00:07:10,415 --> 00:07:10,895
Hello.

131
00:07:19,855 --> 00:07:21,655
(He only spoke out against tyranny,)

132
00:07:22,056 --> 00:07:23,696
(and exposed those speculators)

133
00:07:23,895 --> 00:07:24,535
(and swindlers.)

134
00:07:24,816 --> 00:07:25,696
(He's surely guilty!)

135
00:07:26,376 --> 00:07:27,056
(Shut her up.)

136
00:07:30,176 --> 00:07:31,016
(Enough, miss.)

137
00:07:32,895 --> 00:07:34,335
(Ten lashes for extortion.)

138
00:07:35,376 --> 00:07:37,215
(Malicious slander and defamation...)

139
00:07:37,415 --> 00:07:37,895
Hai.

140
00:07:38,736 --> 00:07:39,136
Hai.

141
00:07:56,568 --> 00:07:57,784
How did you know I was here?

142
00:07:58,136 --> 00:07:58,736
Let me ask you.

143
00:07:59,376 --> 00:08:01,455
Was it you who did that to Mr. Tan?

144
00:08:08,816 --> 00:08:09,335
No.

145
00:08:09,655 --> 00:08:11,016
Then why do you keep dodging me?

146
00:08:31,975 --> 00:08:32,815
- (From now on,)
- From now on,

147
00:08:32,895 --> 00:08:34,376
- (we won't beat innocent people.)
- we won't beat innocent people.

148
00:08:36,616 --> 00:08:38,616
- (We'll show you fair justice.)
- We'll show you fair justice.

149
00:08:46,016 --> 00:08:46,976
I have no choice.

150
00:08:48,575 --> 00:08:49,175
Qiang.

151
00:08:49,895 --> 00:08:51,256
Why did you do this?

152
00:08:51,575 --> 00:08:52,096
For money.

153
00:08:56,175 --> 00:08:57,175
Hai, I won't lie to you.

154
00:08:57,736 --> 00:09:00,575
I've figured out the timing,
supply, and sales channels.

155
00:09:01,096 --> 00:09:02,016
If you join us,

156
00:09:02,775 --> 00:09:03,695
we'll make a fortune.

157
00:09:04,376 --> 00:09:05,815
Do you know what this is?

158
00:09:06,336 --> 00:09:07,415
It's robbery.

159
00:09:07,736 --> 00:09:08,256
A crime!

160
00:09:08,256 --> 00:09:08,976
So what?

161
00:09:12,775 --> 00:09:15,136
You think those 'monkeys'
earn their money clean?

162
00:09:15,575 --> 00:09:17,496
We're robbing the rich to help the poor.

163
00:09:17,976 --> 00:09:19,216
The bolder you are,

164
00:09:19,256 --> 00:09:20,976
the more you get. Hai.

165
00:09:21,976 --> 00:09:24,016
Besides, I'm not doing this forever.

166
00:09:24,336 --> 00:09:26,336
Just make some big ones, and save up.

167
00:09:27,496 --> 00:09:29,856
I'll open a factory myself
and become a 'monkey' too.

168
00:09:29,935 --> 00:09:31,695
Who'd dare look down on us then?

169
00:09:35,216 --> 00:09:36,456
I'm serious.

170
00:09:37,175 --> 00:09:39,055
Keep doing this, you'll get caught.

171
00:09:40,096 --> 00:09:40,655
Stop now.

172
00:09:41,016 --> 00:09:41,655
Stop?

173
00:09:42,775 --> 00:09:43,815
(I'll spare your life.)

174
00:09:44,096 --> 00:09:45,415
Then what should I do?

175
00:09:47,496 --> 00:09:48,815
I work at a state-owned factory.

176
00:09:49,175 --> 00:09:49,935
I'm doing fine.

177
00:09:50,456 --> 00:09:52,415
I'll ask my master

178
00:09:52,895 --> 00:09:54,775
to find you a job there.

179
00:09:54,775 --> 00:09:55,895
Hai.

180
00:09:56,376 --> 00:09:58,695
You've been worked there for long.

181
00:10:00,136 --> 00:10:01,376
What do they pay you monthly?

182
00:10:03,216 --> 00:10:03,935
36 yuan.

183
00:10:05,935 --> 00:10:07,575
You know how much I make each time?

184
00:10:08,456 --> 00:10:09,016
How much?

185
00:10:12,456 --> 00:10:13,055
8,000 yuan.

186
00:10:14,736 --> 00:10:16,695
8,000 yuan, one time.

187
00:10:17,935 --> 00:10:19,336
Ever seen that much money?

188
00:10:20,856 --> 00:10:22,016
(Fight me again.)

189
00:10:22,695 --> 00:10:24,736
(Forgotten? I'm a bandit.)

190
00:10:30,496 --> 00:10:32,056
- (Bandits don't care)
- Bandits don't care

191
00:10:32,056 --> 00:10:33,456
- (how they get results.)
- how they get results.

192
00:10:35,376 --> 00:10:36,695
(I want you kneel down)

193
00:10:37,415 --> 00:10:39,216
(and beg this lady for mercy.)

194
00:10:39,256 --> 00:10:39,775
Qiang.

195
00:10:39,815 --> 00:10:40,575
Hai.

196
00:10:41,575 --> 00:10:42,655
(You're crazy.)

197
00:10:42,856 --> 00:10:45,175
If you can't live with it, turn me in.

198
00:10:47,895 --> 00:10:49,575
If my buddy betrays me, I'll accept it.

199
00:10:49,775 --> 00:10:50,256
(Kneel!)

200
00:10:50,695 --> 00:10:51,295
(I won't!)

201
00:11:01,144 --> 00:11:02,360
(Actively Promote the Five Do's,
Four Upliftings, and Three Loves)

202
00:11:04,415 --> 00:11:05,256
- Stop!
- Stop!

203
00:11:05,535 --> 00:11:06,216
- Duck!
- Duck!

204
00:11:07,016 --> 00:11:07,496
Don't run!

205
00:11:09,935 --> 00:11:10,336
Stop!

206
00:11:12,976 --> 00:11:13,336
Go!

207
00:11:13,535 --> 00:11:13,895
Go!

208
00:11:16,976 --> 00:11:18,376
Zheng Zhiqiang, come with us!

209
00:11:18,935 --> 00:11:19,415
Cuff him.

210
00:11:20,136 --> 00:11:20,695
Behave!

211
00:11:21,895 --> 00:11:22,415
Let me go!

212
00:11:24,632 --> 00:11:26,731
(Pingchuan Wire Factory)

213
00:11:37,055 --> 00:11:38,655
I've told Xuemei long ago

214
00:11:38,815 --> 00:11:42,175
that Xiaohai and those punks
would never reform.

215
00:11:43,336 --> 00:11:44,616
And Zheng Zhiqiang

216
00:11:45,096 --> 00:11:47,055
is even worse than Yang Xiaohai.

217
00:11:48,655 --> 00:11:49,575
Lower your voice.

218
00:11:49,856 --> 00:11:52,055
Forgotten he's Mr. Zheng's nephew?

219
00:11:53,415 --> 00:11:54,216
What's that?

220
00:11:54,935 --> 00:11:56,535
Yang Xiaohai and those punks

221
00:11:56,736 --> 00:11:57,616
were all arrested.

222
00:11:58,856 --> 00:11:59,616
Is that true?

223
00:12:01,720 --> 00:12:03,736
(Severe Crackdown on Highway Bandits:
the Operation's a Success)

224
00:12:04,256 --> 00:12:04,976
Great.

225
00:12:05,895 --> 00:12:07,695
Today's on me.

226
00:12:09,136 --> 00:12:10,415
My treat.

227
00:12:10,895 --> 00:12:12,016
No.

228
00:12:17,256 --> 00:12:17,856
Well...

229
00:12:20,415 --> 00:12:20,976
Decheng.

230
00:12:22,655 --> 00:12:24,535
Your sister-in-law

231
00:12:25,376 --> 00:12:27,016
let me come find you.

232
00:12:35,815 --> 00:12:36,376
Desheng.

233
00:12:39,175 --> 00:12:40,216
Zhiqiang...

234
00:12:40,376 --> 00:12:42,895
I-I know.

235
00:12:44,055 --> 00:12:46,976
I just wanted to ask...

236
00:12:47,456 --> 00:12:52,016
How long might he get?

237
00:12:58,736 --> 00:12:59,288
Well...

238
00:13:00,248 --> 00:13:02,775
The court hasn't ruled yet.

239
00:13:03,376 --> 00:13:04,575
We've consulted documents.

240
00:13:05,456 --> 00:13:06,415
According to the law,

241
00:13:07,695 --> 00:13:08,895
Zhiqiang

242
00:13:10,456 --> 00:13:11,295
may...

243
00:13:18,136 --> 00:13:19,096
get several years.

244
00:13:22,336 --> 00:13:23,895
That long?

245
00:13:26,376 --> 00:13:27,000
Then...

246
00:13:27,608 --> 00:13:28,856
Can it be less?

247
00:13:30,055 --> 00:13:32,935
If he behaves well,
he could be released earlier.

248
00:13:37,655 --> 00:13:42,616
I really wonder
what the conditions are there?

249
00:13:46,016 --> 00:13:48,376
Desheng, I don't know either.

250
00:13:57,336 --> 00:13:57,895
Decheng.

251
00:14:01,935 --> 00:14:03,055
You're the Secretary.

252
00:14:04,935 --> 00:14:05,695
Could...

253
00:14:07,055 --> 00:14:07,864
Could you...

254
00:14:09,048 --> 00:14:09,976
Could you...

255
00:14:12,815 --> 00:14:14,415
Put in a word for him?

256
00:14:15,575 --> 00:14:17,216
Help him, please.

257
00:14:36,055 --> 00:14:36,695
Desheng.

258
00:14:39,096 --> 00:14:40,895
He committed a crime.

259
00:14:43,976 --> 00:14:44,616
Decheng.

260
00:14:46,775 --> 00:14:48,695
I've never asked you
for anything before.

261
00:14:49,856 --> 00:14:51,456
Never asked you.

262
00:14:53,136 --> 00:14:56,575
Zhiqiang committed
such a serious offense.

263
00:14:57,935 --> 00:14:58,295
You...

264
00:15:04,736 --> 00:15:06,295
I'm begging you today.

265
00:15:06,336 --> 00:15:07,295
Desheng, stop.

266
00:15:07,336 --> 00:15:09,096
No, I'm begging you.

267
00:15:09,136 --> 00:15:09,736
Desheng.

268
00:15:09,815 --> 00:15:10,856
Please, I beg you.

269
00:15:10,895 --> 00:15:12,976
Help him, won't you?

270
00:15:13,376 --> 00:15:13,976
Desheng.

271
00:15:14,216 --> 00:15:15,016
Get up.

272
00:15:15,815 --> 00:15:17,535
Desheng, I know.

273
00:15:17,815 --> 00:15:18,856
Desheng, I know.

274
00:15:20,136 --> 00:15:20,856
I know, Desheng.

275
00:15:23,256 --> 00:15:24,736
I know it's difficult for you.

276
00:15:26,815 --> 00:15:28,976
I know Zhiqiang did make a mistake.

277
00:15:29,655 --> 00:15:32,856
That day, I beat him at home.

278
00:15:33,575 --> 00:15:35,736
He realized he was wrong.

279
00:15:37,535 --> 00:15:42,136
Zhiqiang has been closest to you
since he was little.

280
00:15:43,456 --> 00:15:44,935
Now he's in trouble.

281
00:15:45,336 --> 00:15:47,775
You can't just abandon him.

282
00:15:51,655 --> 00:15:55,216
Desheng. I really want to help.

283
00:15:59,295 --> 00:16:01,216
If you'd told me earlier,

284
00:16:03,016 --> 00:16:05,096
I would've taken him to turn himself in.

285
00:16:06,016 --> 00:16:07,704
T-Then, things...

286
00:16:08,472 --> 00:16:10,216
